Technical Feature Proposal: Improved CFS Attendance Module (US-CFS-ATT-001)

1. Strategic Feature Context

Vision Statement To transform Child Friendly Space (CFS) operations from retrospective monthly reporting to high-fidelity, real-time session tracking, enabling immediate protection interventions and automated donor compliance for SSWOCO and War Child Holland.

The Donor Automated Report Technology (DART) platform is designed to replace manual, Excel-based tracking with a unified digital ecosystem. For the Child Friendly Space (CFS) module, the primary high-frequency interaction is "CFS session attendance." Currently, SSWOCO operates four CFS locations across Sectors 1–4 of the Malakal Protection of Civilians (PoC) site. This proposal focuses on moving away from fragmented monthly presence logs to a session-level recording system that captures the "who, when, and where" of child protection activities. By digitizing this touchpoint, we ensure that SSWOCO meets the rigorous reporting requirements of War Child Holland while providing a foundation for real-time case identification.

2. User Story Definition: US-CFS-ATT-001

User Story "As a Facilitator (Peter), I want to quickly mark which children are present at each session by tapping their names on my device so that attendance is recorded without slowing down the start of the session."

Background: Facilitators previously relied on a 982-row Excel database, which led to significant data lag and reporting errors. By shifting to real-time session-level tracking, DART allows for granular data collection (distinguishing between TeamUp psychosocial support, General Group activities, and Children Sessions) without adding administrative burden to field staff.

3. Design Philosophy: The "5-Tap" Speed Architecture

To ensure adoption in high-pressure field environments, the attendance module is built on the "Speed Above All" constraint. The goal is for a facilitator to initiate a session in under ten seconds.

The 5-Tap Flow:

Tap 1: Select 'Take attendance' from the dashboard.

Tap 2: Confirm the date (defaults to Today).

Tap 3: Select Session Type (supports: General group activity, TeamUp, or Children Sessions).

Tap 4: Confirm Location (pre-filled from user's active assignment).

Tap 5: Tap 'Start' to load the child list.

