7. Feature Logic & Acceptance Criteria

The following functional behaviors are mandatory for the successful delivery of US-CFS-ATT-001:

[ ] Prerequisite Mapping: The pre-population of the session location and active children depends on a valid entry in the user_location_assignments table. Peter must be assigned to a sector before recording.

[ ] Smart Pre-population: Session date defaults to "Today," and the location is locked to the facilitator’s active assignment.

[ ] Alphabetical Tap List: The child list must load from IndexedDB and display all beneficiaries registered at the current location, sorted alphabetically by personal name.

[ ] Toggling Presence: Tapping a child's name marks them present (Green highlight); un-tapped children are submitted as "absent."

[ ] Duplicate Detection: If a session record for the same date/type/location already exists, the system must prompt the user to "Add to" or "Replace" data, handling the 409 server response.

[ ] Sync Indicators: A real-time badge must show the count of unsynced records on the dashboard.

8. Case Identification & Referral Integration (US-CFS-ATT-002)

Facilitators have access to a "Flag" mechanism, enabling Peter to identify a child in distress without interrupting the attendance flow.

Technical Note on Notifications: Push notifications are not available in Version 1. The Case Worker (Regina) is notified via an unreviewed flags badge count on her dashboard, which refreshes during manual sync actions.

The Flag Lifecycle:

pending_review: Flag created by Facilitator; awaiting Case Worker review.

reviewed_case_opened: Case Worker (Regina) has initiated a formal Case Management record.

reviewed_no_action: Case Worker determined no further intervention is required.

reviewed_referred: Case Worker has referred the child to an external service.

